<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870612-0106 </DOCNO><HL> Financial Services ConcernClears Buyback of Notes</HL><DD> 06/12/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GAMIBUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK) </IN><DATELINE> CHICAGO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Great American Management andamp; Investment Inc. said its board has authorized the buyback of as much as $16 million of its 14% and 15 3/4% subordinated notes.    The financial services concern said it will pay holders face value of the notes and accrued interest to the date of the purchase. The offer, which isn't conditioned upon a minimum amount of the notes being acquired, expires July 17.    The company is also soliciting consents from holders of the notes to amend its indenture with IBJ Schroder Bank andamp; Trust Co. Holders consenting to the amendment by June 30 will be paid $10 per $1,000 face amount of notes. After that the company will pay that amount only to the extent that consents are needed for approval of the amendment. </TEXT></DOC>